<paragraph id="A25856D1109B19F1E92FD98DA972C4FA" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">Kleefarn</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="666A2145996225AD9763448A0A061917" pageId="null" pageNumber="147" type="description">
<paragraph id="7C3004F16E82CD3BCB6C2D81023F2DDD" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">
<normalizedToken id="793D06C3E9CA51BE79245768D108C3B3" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
lang gestielt, 
<emphasis id="3C41E869CE002078B762EFBDBA80FCD0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">
mit 4teiliger, 
<normalizedToken id="B894FFDEF55FAB47FA09EA0077E81666" originalValue="kleeblattähnlicher" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">kleeblattaehnlicher</normalizedToken>
Spreite.
</emphasis>
Sporokarpien am Grunde des Blattstiels auf kurzen Stielen zu 2-25, 
<normalizedToken id="DBD74FF0A2090F389DDDBEE8E178C12E" originalValue="bohnenförmig" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">bohnenfoermig</normalizedToken>
, behaart oder verkahlend, mit 4-24 
<normalizedToken id="AACD08B10A884FE34BED023995D85929" originalValue="Fächern" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">Faechern</normalizedToken>
(in jedem Fach Makro- und Mikrosporangien), 2klappig aufspringend.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6DF0D0EF09F4527DE98CE08F4475A4B9" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">
Die Gattung 
<emphasis id="A94D7C1490606FDDA135BCA008F2F345" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">
<normalizedToken id="A6A81A128D9E68D70FD6D1AEF7606C1E" originalValue="umfaβt" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">umfaβt</normalizedToken>
etwa 70 Arten und ist in tropischen und subtropischen Zonen verbreitet.
</emphasis>
In 
<taxonomicName id="8C07A13E957FC4AFC958F72E92121E5B" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Europa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Europa</taxonomicName>
2 Arten, im Gebiet nur 
<emphasis id="5413CC3A6A1F258836605FEE6323EAC8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">
<taxonomicName id="80F4284FEDDDEB0A44A1752E5D09B13C" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Marsileaceae" genus="Marsilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Salviniales" pageId="null" pageNumber="147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="quadrifolia">M. quadrifolia</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
In der Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="0D97BADABC188FAE8240BC7BF6DE42E9" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Marsileaceae" genus="Marsilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Salviniales" pageId="null" pageNumber="147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F48316B5CCCA895F041A0D47321B7B71" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">Marsilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ist 
<emphasis id="9EAF34AF14961A6BE5EE3982D8FB8AD5" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">Apomixis</emphasis>
nachgewiesen (Strasburger 1907). Moderne zytologische Untersuchungen an einer indischen Art (
<taxonomicName id="AFF7E48307F46BEA4ABBB2B14DD6EA98" authority="L." authorityName="L." class="Polypodiopsida" family="Marsileaceae" genus="Marsilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Salviniales" pageId="null" pageNumber="147" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="F22835E7457E7F1882E2A3543507B097" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">Marsilia minuta</emphasis>
<authorityName id="92BFCB9D7089FF4964C06A861C42F27D" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">L.</authorityName>
</taxonomicName>
): 
<emphasis id="82D1A4A0729BC276F3E9662D036DB4CE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">polyploide Reihe</emphasis>
mit 2n = 40, 60, 
<normalizedToken id="8BBD89D4EF63D28B2A347E38545A70F6" originalValue="gestörte" pageId="null" pageNumber="147">gestoerte</normalizedToken>
sexuelle Fortpflanzung (Mehra und Loyal 1958).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
